rComments: Great course to take. Although there are many readings, most of them are quite short. There are a couple essays (very short) you have to write, a small presentation and 20% is participation. Overall a great elective with interesting topics (19-20th century literature + some modern short stories). Small lecture size is also great.

Amazing professor! It was very interesting to take his courses since I don't have literature background. Eye opening experience. A lot of readings but if you put in some effort you're guaranteed an A or a B+. Prof helps you to analyze literature in a way you couldn't imagine before. It develops your communication/writing skills as well. Recommend!

One of the best professors I've ever had. He makes the class very interesting, there is a lot of reading that you have to do (approximately a book a read) but if you enjoy Slavic and Ukrainian studies this is a class worth taking. His classes are almost entirely discussion based.
